From 7d6fd92a1b3c8b4fa28a2e9f272793ffcd0a5482 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Marek Vasut <marex@denx.de>
Date: Sat, 15 Feb 2020 17:54:19 +0100
Subject: [PATCH 47/73] net: ks8851-ml: Fix 16-bit IO operation

[ Upstream commit 58292104832fef6cb4a89f736012c0e0724c3442 ]

The Micrel KSZ8851-16MLLI datasheet DS00002357B page 12 states that
BE[3:0] signals are active high. This contradicts the measurements
of the behavior of the actual chip, where these signals behave as
active low. For example, to read the CIDER register, the bus must
expose 0xc0c0 during the address phase, which means BE[3:0]=4'b1100.

